---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Support - Leszek Pomianowski">
  <div class="page">
    <h1>Professional Support</h1>
    <p>
      Get expert guidance and support for WPF UI, modern Windows development, and related technologies. 
      Our support plans are designed to help teams and organizations successfully implement and maintain 
      modern Windows applications.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Support Plans</h2>
    
    <h3>Community Support (Free)</h3>
    <p>For open-source projects and individual developers:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>GitHub Issues and Discussions for WPF UI and other projects</li>
      <li>Community-driven support through GitHub</li>
      <li>Documentation and examples</li>
      <li>Best effort response time</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Individual developers, open-source projects, learning</p>
    
    <h3>Priority Email Support</h3>
    <p>Professional email support for development teams:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Priority response to technical questions (24-48 hours)</li>
      <li>Implementation guidance and best practices</li>
      <li>Troubleshooting assistance</li>
      <li>Architecture recommendations</li>
      <li>Migration planning and support</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> 24-48 hours during business days</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Small to medium development teams, startups</p>
    
    <h3>Professional Consulting</h3>
    <p>Comprehensive consulting services for organizations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Everything in Priority Email Support</li>
      <li>Video consultation sessions</li>
      <li>Code review and optimization</li>
      <li>Custom implementation guidance</li>
      <li>Team training and workshops</li>
      <li>Performance optimization</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> 12-24 hours during business days</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Growing organizations, complex implementations</p>
    
    <h3>Enterprise Support</h3>
    <p>Dedicated support for large organizations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Everything in Professional Consulting</li>
      <li>Dedicated support channel</li>
      <li>On-site consultation (when possible)</li>
      <li>Custom development services</li>
      <li>SLA agreements</li>
      <li>Priority feature development</li>
      <li>Emergency support options</li>
    </ul>
    <p><strong>Response Time:</strong> 4-8 hours during business days</p>
    <p><strong>Best for:</strong> Large enterprises, mission-critical applications</p>
    
    <h2>What's Included</h2>
    
    <h3>Technical Expertise</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>WPF UI Implementation</strong> - Best practices for modern Windows applications</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Optimization</strong> - Ensuring smooth, responsive user experiences</li>
      <li><strong>Architecture Guidance</strong> - Scalable patterns for complex applications</li>
      <li><strong>Migration Support</strong> - Moving from legacy UI frameworks to modern solutions</li>
      <li><strong>Custom Theming</strong> - Brand-specific design implementations</li>
      <li><strong>Accessibility</strong> - Ensuring applications work for all users</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h3>Development Services</h3>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Code Review</strong> - Expert analysis of your WPF implementations</li>
      <li><strong>Performance Audits</strong> - Identifying and resolving bottlenecks</li>
      <li><strong>Training Programs</strong> - Upskilling your development team</li>
      <li><strong>Documentation</strong> - Creating comprehensive implementation guides</li>
      <li><strong>Testing Strategy</strong> - Automated testing approaches for WPF applications</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Technologies Covered</h2>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>WPF UI</strong> - Complete support for all library features and implementations</li>
      <li><strong>WPF Framework</strong> - Traditional and modern WPF development patterns</li>
      <li><strong>.NET Technologies</strong> - .NET Framework, .NET Core, .NET 5+</li>
      <li><strong>MVVM Patterns</strong> - Model-View-ViewModel architecture and best practices</li>
      <li><strong>Data Binding</strong> - Advanced binding scenarios and performance optimization</li>
      <li><strong>Custom Controls</strong> - Creating and maintaining custom UI components</li>
      <li><strong>Theming and Styling</strong> - Advanced customization and branding</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Success Stories</h2>
    <p>Organizations using our professional support have achieved:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>50% faster development cycles</strong> through expert guidance and best practices</li>
      <li><strong>Improved application performance</strong> with optimization recommendations</li>
      <li><strong>Reduced bug counts</strong> through proper architecture and code review</li>
      <li><strong>Enhanced user satisfaction</strong> with modern, accessible interfaces</li>
      <li><strong>Successful migrations</strong> from legacy frameworks to modern WPF</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Getting Started</h2>
    <p>Ready to get professional support for your WPF development?</p>
    
    <h3>Contact Process</h3>
    <ol>
      <li><strong>Initial Consultation</strong> - Contact us to discuss your needs</li>
      <li><strong>Requirements Assessment</strong> - We'll evaluate your project and requirements</li>
      <li><strong>Custom Proposal</strong> - Receive a tailored support plan</li>
      <li><strong>Onboarding</strong> - Quick setup and immediate access to support</li>
    </ol>
    
    <h3>Contact Information</h3>
    <p>
      To discuss support options and pricing, please contact us at:
      <br><strong>support at lepo.co</strong>
    </p>
    <p>
      Please replace "at" with @ when sending your email. Include information about:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Your project scope and timeline</li>
      <li>Team size and technical background</li>
      <li>Specific challenges or requirements</li>
      <li>Preferred support level</li>
    </ul>
    
    <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>
    
    <h3>What technologies do you support?</h3>
    <p>
      We specialize in WPF UI, modern WPF development, .NET technologies, and related Windows 
      development frameworks. Our expertise covers everything from basic implementations to 
      complex enterprise applications.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Do you provide on-site consulting?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes, on-site consulting is available for Enterprise Support customers, subject to 
      scheduling and location. Remote consulting via video calls is available for all paid support tiers.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Can you help with existing applications?</h3>
    <p>
      Absolutely! We can help optimize existing WPF applications, migrate from legacy frameworks, 
      implement modern design patterns, and improve performance.
    </p>
    
    <h3>What is your response time commitment?</h3>
    <p>
      Response times vary by support tier: Priority Email (24-48 hours), Professional Consulting 
      (12-24 hours), and Enterprise Support (4-8 hours). All times are during business days.
    </p>
    
    <h3>Do you offer custom development?</h3>
    <p>
      Yes, custom development services are available for Professional Consulting and Enterprise 
      Support customers. This includes custom controls, specialized implementations, and 
      application development.
    </p>
    
    <h2>Open Source Commitment</h2>
    <p>
      Professional support services help sustain the open-source ecosystem by funding continued 
      development of WPF UI and related projects. All core libraries remain free and open-source, 
      and community support continues to be available through GitHub.
    </p>
    
    <p>
      By choosing professional support, you're not only getting expert help for your projects 
      but also contributing to the continued development and maintenance of tools that benefit 
      the entire .NET development community.
    </p>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

